===Etymology===
[[File:Streisand Estate.jpg|thumb|{{w|California Coastal Records Project}} photo of coastline including Streisand Estate (2002).]]

Coined in 2005, after a 2003 incident in which singer [[w:Barbra Streisand|Barbra Streisand]] attempted to have a picture of her house removed from a public collection of 12,000 images documenting [[w:California Coastal Records Project|coastal erosion in California]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|sg=Streisand [[effect]]}}

# A [[phenomenon]] in which attempting to [[suppress]] an item of [[information]] attracts additional [[unwanted]] [[attention]] to it, thus furthering the [[spreading]] of the information.
